article.headline: Princeton 59, Tulane 51
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Judson Wallace scored 20 of his 22 points in the second half to help Princeton beat Tulane 59-51 on Monday night in the Sun Bowl Tournament. Princeton (6-3) advanced to play Texas-El Paso in the championship game. The Miners beat Alabama State 89-57. Wallace scored 20 of Princeton's 24 second-half points. Will Venable added 11 points for the Tigers. Vytas Tatarunas had 15 points and 11 rebounds for Tulane (4-5).
